  "body": "If a chart contains a template like this (will only work on Kubernetes v1.7.0 and above):\r\n\r\n```yaml\r\napiVersion: apiregistration.k8s.io/v1beta1\r\nkind: APIService\r\nmetadata:\r\n  name: v1alpha1.servicecatalog.k8s.io\r\nspec:\r\n  group: servicecatalog.k8s.io\r\n  version: v1alpha1\r\n  service:\r\n    namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}\r\n    name: {{ template \"fullname\" . }}-apiserver\r\n  caBundle: {{ (.Files.Get .Values.apiserver.tls.caFileName) | b64enc }}\r\n  priority: 100\r\n  groupPriorityMinimum: 10000\r\n  versionPriority: 20\r\n```\r\n\r\n... the output of `kubectl get apiservice` will include `v1alpha1.servicecatalog.k8s.io`. When a user runs a `helm delete ...` command, the `APIService` will still exist in this list, which means that a subsequent `helm install` command will fail. Personally, I think it makes sense to delete the `APIService` on a `helm delete` command.\r\n\r\nI'd be interested to hear others' thoughts as well!",
